<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="620" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.51/210.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Guatemalan Government has been informed that the British Government
                            refuses to consider a just arrangement for converting the external debt
                            of Guatemala and thereby make it possible to reorganize the finances and
                            currency of that country, and is painfully surprised thereat. If the
                            Department considers it advisable the Guatemalan Government will send a
                            special financial and diplomatic agent to London. The Foreign Office
                            desires to know whether you have any advices since December 28,
                            1912.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hitt</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>